---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Korea Visa & Entry Guide for Visitors"
  description="A plain-English overview of visa-free entry, K-ETA, and entry requirements for visiting Korea — plus where to check the rules for your nationality."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Essentials</p>
      <h1>Visa & Entry for Korea</h1>
      <p>Start here, then confirm the details for your nationality.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="article wrap">
    <div class="prose">
      <blockquote>
        Visa and entry rules change often and depend on your nationality. This
        page is a starting point, not legal advice — always confirm with an
        official source before you book.
      </blockquote>

      <h2>The three things to check</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Do you need a visa?</strong> Many nationalities can enter
          visa-free for short tourism stays; others need a visa in advance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Do you need K-ETA?</strong> The Korea Electronic Travel
          Authorization is an online pre-approval some visa-free travelers must
          get before boarding. Check whether it currently applies to you.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Passport validity & onward ticket</strong> — have a passport
          valid for your stay and proof of onward/return travel.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-box">
      <h4>Where to check — official sources</h4>
      <div class="fact-grid">
        <div class="fact"><span class="k">K-ETA</span><span class="v">k-eta.go.kr</span></div>
        <div class="fact"><span class="k">Visa portal</span><span class="v">visa.go.kr</span></div>
        <div class="fact"><span class="k">In person</span><span class="v">Your Korean embassy</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="disclosure">
      We deliberately do not list per-country rules here because they change
      frequently. Verify your specific case on the official government sites
      above. This is general information, not immigration advice.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
